Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Sands Beach
Description: This is my favorite beach to visit as a UCSB student. It's the perfect location to practice surfing and watch the sunset that sets directly in front of the beach. I once sat here, read a book for my religious studies class and watched the sunset, it was one of the most tranquil experiences I've ever had.

Name: Whitewater Preserve
Description: This is my favorite place to hike back near my hometown. There's beautiful sprawling hills, wild mountain goats, tortoises, and toads everywhere. I started hiking here after I took a field trip here for my AP Environmental Science class in high school and me and my friends crossed the river (which is not advised to do due to the currents) and it was a lot of fun.

Name: Redondo Beach Pier
Description: I visited this pier a lot with my family as this was the area my mother gre up in. I have a lot of memories of just staying in the old kinda run-down arcade and they have a tilt-a-whirl ride in it that was a lot of fun.

Name: Mount San Jacinto
Description: This is the main mountain that overlooks the Coachella Valley where I'm from. In third grade we got to go up an aerial tramway and go sledding in the snow up on the mountain. The tramway was very scary and made many people cry cause we were all like 8 years old.

Name: Rancho Mirage High School
Description: This is where I went to high school. I was the third class to ever graduate from the school, so the school was very nice and clean which was nice. All of the teachers there were very supportive and helpful, and I'm so glad I got to go to high school here
